West Bromwich Albion beat Crystal Palace 2-0 at Selhurst Park on Saturday . 
  James Morrison headed the away side ahead after just two minutes . 
  Craig Gardner scored the second goal of the game with a fine long range effort . 
  Tony Pulis returned to the Eagles for the first time since leaving the club in the summer . 
  Alan Pardew lost his first game in charge of the Eagles . 
  The Baggies remain in the Premier League relegation zone . 
 